+{"id":"frankenjax-jw63","title":"Reshape silently wraps oversized new_shape dims","description":"[HIGH] crates/fj-lax/src/tensor_ops.rs eval_reshape parses the new_shape parameter as i64 but casts non-negative dimensions with `as u32` before checking range. This is still present at lines 401-414 for scalar inputs and lines 445-479 for tensor inputs. A requested dimension above u32::MAX silently wraps instead of returning EvalError, which is the same bug class recently fixed for BroadcastInDim/Concatenate/Pad output shapes.\n\nRepro: construct an empty tensor with `TensorValue::new(DType::I64, Shape { dims: vec![0] }, vec![])`, wrap it as `Value::Tensor`, set params `{ \"new_shape\": \"4294967296\" }`, and call `eval_primitive(Primitive::Reshape, &[input], &params)`. Current code casts 4294967296 to 0, computes total 0, and can return shape `[0]` instead of rejecting the impossible requested shape. Scalar reshape has the same unchecked cast path and can also mis-handle out-of-range dimensions before validating product.\n\nExpected: reject negative and out-of-u32-range dims before casting, use checked multiplication for known/output products, reject inferred dimensions that exceed u32::MAX, and add regression tests for `new_shape=4294967296` plus product overflow cases that do not allocate.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T08:42:51.444674474Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T08:42:51.444674474Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
